org.openbel.framework.common.external
Interface CachingExternalizable

All Superinterfaces:
Externalizable, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AnnotationDefinitionTable, AnnotationDefinitionTable.TableAnnotationDefinition, AnnotationValueTable, AnnotationValueTable.TableAnnotationValue, DocumentTable, DocumentTable.DocumentHeader, ExternalType, NamespaceTable, NamespaceTable.TableNamespace, ParameterTable, ParameterTable.TableParameter, ProtoEdgeTable, ProtoEdgeTable.TableProtoEdge, ProtoNetwork, ProtoNodeTable, StatementAnnotationMapTable, StatementAnnotationMapTable.AnnotationPair, StatementTable, StatementTable.TableStatement, TermParameterMapTable, TermTable
public interface CachingExternalizable
extends Externalizable

Describes a reference type that can be stored and retrieved from object I/O.

Hash-based caching is paramount in storing and retrieving external types. The use of these caches allow us to minimize the amount of reads and writes during externalizing operations.

This interface needs to be redesigned. Original use of ReadCache and WriteCache objects used by the interface is no longer really suitable.

Since:
1.3
